For only the second time in the past 20 seasons, the game will feature the No. 1 seed in each conference (Super Bowl XLIV: New Orleans vs. Indianapolis in the 2009 season). Super Bowl XLVIII will pit the NFL's top offense (Denver) against the league's best defense (Seattle).
